      "date": "2011-12-31 14:17:41.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(1 inline comment)\n\nWhen fixing (trailing, at least) whitespace errors, it's usually a good idea to just fix the whole file at once instead of just the few lines that have been pointed out within gerrit's context.\n\nIf you use vim for example:\n\n:g/[ ^I][ ^I]*$/s///g\n\nwill strip the trailing spaces from every line.\n\nNote that the ^I in that expression above is a \"tab\", not a caret and an `I'. You get that in vim by typing control-v then hitting tab.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
